{#
  Content-gap markers. Every design-authored passage that is NOT backed by a
  reviewed dossier or the July source (a2b640) renders as a visible
  [CONTENT NEEDED: <field>] marker rather than invented filler (founder
  condition 6). The <field> slug groups gaps across pages: the grouped gap
  list in the PR is generated by grepping data-gap="<slug>", so all pages that
  need the same field (e.g. every detail page needing a "cta") are one task.

  block(): a full-width gap where a whole section's copy is missing.
  inline(): a gap inside a line (a heading, a one-line summary).
  Keep slugs kebab-case and field-shaped ("sector-worked-example"), not
  page-shaped, so grouping-by-field works.
#}
{% macro block(slug, note="") -%}
<div class="content-needed" data-gap="{{ slug }}" role="note">[CONTENT NEEDED: {{ slug }}]{% if note %} — {{ note }}{% endif %}</div>
{%- endmacro %}

{% macro inline(slug) -%}
<span class="content-needed content-needed--inline" data-gap="{{ slug }}">[CONTENT NEEDED: {{ slug }}]</span>
{%- endmacro %}
